organic_results.title: The effects of perceptions of the academic job market on adjunct faculty: An identity-theory analysis
organic_results.snippet: Declining enrollments and financial considerations have caused institutions of higher education to employ an ever-increasing number of part-time (adjunct) faculty members. This article reports on a study of the social-psychological effects of the declining academic labor market on 515 adjunct faculty members teaching transfer-level courses in two-year community colleges in northern Illinois and southern Wisconsin.
